cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.AL

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper is about a new data structure called position heaps and presents several algorithmic results related to it.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of position heaps for pattern matching, which is a common task in information retrieval.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possible category as the paper involves analyzing the worst-case cost of insertions and deletions in position heaps, which can be seen as a combinatorial problem.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper discusses the time complexity of building a position heap and simulating it using a compressed suffix array.
- cs.AL (Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents new algorithms for position heaps.
